The paper deals with source coding with side information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Gaussian distributions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The problem of encoding information with side information is also relevant to the field of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper involves characterizing the rate-distortion region, which is a topic in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with jointly Gaussian distributions, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
